= Biju Mathew
== Member, Indian Civil Liberties Union (ICWI)

I am so sorry to hear this news and I hope that Ila and you find the strength to live through this moment in all the stories and memories that you carry of Deepak.

I am devastated by this news. I had written to Deepak 3 or 4 weeks ago regarding some ICWI matters and when I didn't hear back from him I had begun to get worried. And I even ended up calling Vinod and somewhere in that conversation asked gently if he knew how Deepak was doing. And I kept telling myself that I should keep the worry aside and that while there was a health condition to be concerned about, it was something that we would all support Deepak through over the next many years.

I did not know Deepak very well even though he was part of our circles till 5 years ago when he joined ICWI and played a really important role in helping with the Bhima Koregaon forensic investigation. He became the person I would reach out to, to understand the technicalities, and he put me in touch with several people who have played a crucial role in that project. After that, from 2022 my conversations with him continued. Just recently, I heard from Bharat Rathore, an ICWI member who has built a very significant mentoring network called the Bahujans Scholar Network, that he was overjoyed at the news that Deepak had joined as a mentor and was helping a whole group of Bahujan CS students in India figure out career pathways. Deepak was actively thinking about caste when the initial ICWI work groups were being formed — he was the first one to volunteer for the anti-caste work-group. And when he moved to New York I was overjoyed, hoping to get to know him a lot better. But kya kare... that hope will never be realized. We will miss you, comrade.

