= Pedro, Maria Rosa, Dani and Marta
== Collaborator and Friend · IMDEA Software Institute & Polytechnic University of Madrid

I am deeply sorry for the passing of your husband and father, Deepak Kapur. He was someone I cared about very much, and so did my family. I had the great privilege of working with him during several visits I made to UNM in Albuquerque, and also during his visits to Madrid, to the IMDEA Software Institute and the Polytechnic University of Madrid, over the years.

Dear Ila, I believe we have not had the chance to meet, but Deepak spoke to me about you often, always with pride and affection. I am truly sorry that my first message to you comes under such sad circumstances.

I am very grateful for your kindness and hospitality during all my visits to Albuquerque, some of them with my children, Dani and Marta. We deeply appreciated your invitations to your home and the meals we shared, and the warmth with which you always treated us. We hold very fond memories of the time we spent together. I am also grateful for the affection Deepak showed my family when he came to Madrid.

There are two matters I would like to mention whenever you feel ready. First, on the 7th, Deepak contacted me to ask for advice on transferring money from a Banco Santander account in Madrid to a dollar account in the United States. We had arranged to speak over Zoom on Saturday the 11th. When he did not reply to my last message, I became concerned and feared the worst. I can forward you our exchange of messages if you wish.

Second, Deepak and I had been working on a draft of a joint paper which we did not fully complete. I would very much like to finish it and submit it somewhere, with Deepak as first author. For me, this would be a way of honoring him and fulfilling a commitment I made to him. I would, of course, want to do this with your approval.

I am attaching two photos of Deepak that I took during our visit to Aranjuez in June 2014. Please know that you have friends here for anything you may need.

